  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean water for 442 households in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean water is essential for good health.  Right now 55% of households across Kericho county, Kenya have to use dirty water from rivers and ponds.  Access to clean water and good sanitation is a basic human right.  This project will support 2 key areas - protection schemes for 4 natural spring water sources serving 442 households with a population of 2,260 and protecting childrens&apos; health in over 300 schools through provision of rain water harvesting, toilets and handwashing stations.</narrative>
  </description>
